  (47,'Sports','/Files/News/News471493036357812.jpg','‘Chelsea have the edge, but we have NOT given up!’ – Tottenham still believe they can win Premier League title, says goalkeeper Hugo Lloris','Hugo Lloris admits Chelsea''s FA Cup victory could give them renewed belief in the Premier League title race, but insists Tottenham have NOT given up just yet.  Spurs hoped to gain a psychological boost at Wembley by continuing the Blues'' recent dip in form while extending their own excellent run of seven victories on the bounce. Instead, however, Chelsea clinched a dramatic 4-2 win to book their place in the FA Cup final and reassert their status as England’s top team.','2017-04-24','1:51:00','http://talksport.com/football/chelsea-have-edge-we-have-not-given-tottenham-still-believe-they-can-win-premier-league','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (48,'Sports','/Files/News/News481493036358687.jpg','Manchester City HAVE made progress under Pep Guardiola this season, former captain Richard Dunne tells talkSPORT','Richard Dunne insists Manchester City have made progress under Pep Guardiola. Defeat to Arsenal in Sunday''s FA Cup semi-final at Wembley means Guardiola will finish his first season as City boss without any silverware. The club also faces a battle to secure Champions League qualification - defeat to bitter rivals Manchester United on Thursday would see them drop out of the top four spots.','2017-04-24','9:44:00','http://talksport.com/football/manchester-city-have-made-progress-under-pep-guardiola-season-former-captain-richard-dunne','Alex Varney','Active'),
  (49,'Sports','/Files/News/News491493036359390.jpg','''Giving up is not an option'' - Manchester United striker Zlatan Ibrahimovic insists he is not planning to retire despite serious knee injury','Zlatan Ibrahimovic has ruled out retiring from football despite his serious knee injury, with the Manchester United striker vowing: \"I will come back even stronger\". The 35-year-old Swede is facing a lengthy spell on the sidelines after suffering \"significant knee-ligament damage\" during Thursday''s Europa League win over Anderlecht.','2017-04-24','7:14:00','http://talksport.com/football/giving-not-option-manchester-united-striker-zlatan-ibrahimovic-insists-he-not-planning','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (50,'Sports','/Files/News/News501493036360218.jpg','VIDEO: Real Madrid 2-3 Barcelona: Lionel Messi hits late winner to reignite LaLiga title race','Lionel Messi scored his 500th Barcelona goal as his stoppage-time winner against 10-man Real Madrid breathed life into his side''s title challenge. Messi - sporting a black eye and damaged teeth following Marcelo''s first-half challenge - struck twice in a dramatic 3-2 win to take Barcelona to the top of LaLiga. Ivan Rakitic was also on target for Barcelona, while Casemiro and James Rodriguez - the Colombian having equalised in the 85th minute - scored for hosts Real, who had captain Sergio Ramos sent off in the final quarter.','2017-04-23','1:10:00','http://talksport.com/football/video-real-madrid-2-3-barcelona-lionel-messi-hits-late-winner-reignite-laliga-title-race','talkSPORT','Active'),
