  (866,'Sports','/Files/News/News471493812345430.jpg','Everton confirm Aaron Lennon being treated for stress-related illness after winger detained under the Mental Health Act','Everton footballer Aaron Lennon has been detained under the Mental Health Act amid concern for his welfare. The 30-year-old, who has 21 caps for England, was taken to hospital on Sunday to be assessed after officers were called to a road in Salford. His club said he was being treated for a \"stress-related illness\" and his representative urged him to \"stay strong\". The footballer last played for Everton as a substitute in the goalless draw at Middlesbrough on February 11.','2017-05-03','6:57:00','http://talksport.com/football/everton-confirm-aaron-lennon-being-treated-stress-related-illness-after-winger-detained','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (867,'Sports','/Files/News/News481493812346306.jpg','Slaven Bilic set to remain in charge of West Ham beyond this season - talkSPORT sources','West Ham are NOT planning to replace manager Slaven Bilic this summer, talkSPORT understands. Bilic has found himself under pressure after a difficult second season in charge of the London club. The Hammers, who finished seventh in the Premier League in 2015/16, are set to finish in the bottom half of the table this time around. They have lost 16 of their 35 league games and are not yet mathematically safe from relegation. Reports have emerged this week that Bilic''s position is under review and he may be shown the door.','2017-05-03','8:17:00','http://talksport.com/football/slaven-bilic-set-remain-charge-west-ham-beyond-season-talksport-sources-170503237693','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (868,'Sports','/Files/News/News491493812347181.jpg','Cristiano Ronaldo can play at the top level with Real Madrid for AT LEAST four more years – Ramon Calderon on talkSPORT','Cristiano Ronaldo is one of Real Madrid’s greatest ever players and can keep playing at the top level with the club for AT LEAST four more years. That’s the opinion of former Real Madrid president Ramon Calderon, who joined talkSPORT on Wednesday to react to the Portuguese superstar’s heroics in the Champions League semi-finals.','2017-05-03','0:25:00','http://talksport.com/football/cristiano-ronaldo-can-play-top-level-real-madrid-least-four-more-years-ramon-calderon','talkSPORT','Active'),
