  (1483,'Sports','/Files/News/News571494234623771.jpg','Podcast: Danny Kelly''s Trans Europe Express - Sunday, May 7','Danny Kelly is joined by Mark Langdon to take a look at all the big football news from the continent. They discuss Tony Adams’ continuing struggles with lowly Granada – take in action from France, Italy and Spain, and chat about the goalkeepers who are likely to be on the move during the summer transfer window. This week’s European cult hero is the former Real Zaragoza and Paraguay goalkeeper José Luis Chilavert, and there''s also time to preview the second-legs of both the Champions League and Europa League semi-finals.','2017-05-07','3:38:00','http://talksport.com/football/podcast-danny-kellys-trans-europe-express-sunday-may-7-170508238258','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (1484,'Sports','/Files/News/News581494234625626.png','The Press Pass - Sunday, May 7','Neil Ashton is joined by Darren Lewis and Dominic Fifield to cast their eyes over the main sporting stories. The trio look back at an eventful weekend of action, including West Ham ruining Tottenham’s hopes of winning the Premier League title and Arsene Wenger getting one over his old foe Jose Mourinho at the Emirates.   Plus, the panel discuss the ongoing relegation battle and the ups and downs across the Football League.','2017-05-07','3:32:00','http://talksport.com/football/press-pass-sunday-may-7-170508238254','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (1485,'Sports','/Files/News/News591494234627767.jpg','Juventus defender Mehdi Benatia receives apology after ending interview over racist insult','Italian broadcaster Rai has apologised after Juventus defender Medhi Benatia cut a television interview short after claiming to hear a racist insult in his earpiece. The 30-year-old Morocco international, who was born in France, was speaking to reporters following Juve''s 1-1 league draw with Torino on Saturday, when he ended the interview abruptly. Footage published on gazzetta.it shows Benatia saying: \"Which stupid person is speaking? They called me a s***** little Moroccan.\" He had been discussing disciplinary decisions during the game.','2017-05-07','0:27:33','http://talksport.com/football/juventus-defender-mehdi-benatia-receives-apology-after-ending-interview-over-racist-insult','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (1486,'Sports','/Files/News/News601494234628777.jpg','Indian Premier League: Gujarat Lions end three-match losing streak with win over Kings XI Punjab','Gujarat Lions put an end to their three-match losing streak after they chased down the 190-run target set by Kings XI Punjab. Blitzes from opener Dwayne Smith and skipper Suresh Raina powered the Lions to victory, before Dinesh Karthik helped the team get across the finish line with two balls remaining in the innings. LIVE ON talkSPORT 2: Sunrisers Hyderabad v Mumbai Indians on Monday [May 8] from 15:30.','2017-05-07','0:09:42','http://talksport.com/cricket/indian-premier-league-gujarat-lions-end-three-match-losing-streak-win-over-kings-xi-punjab','talkSPORT','Active'),
