  (2169,'Sports','/Files/News/News431495175247592.jpg','Leicester 1-6 Tottenham: Harry Kane bags four goals to take charge of Golden Boot race','Ruthless Harry Kane struck four goals as Tottenham dismantled Leicester 6-1.  The England forward''s haul moved him two ahead of Romelu Lukaku in the race for the Premier League''s golden boot with 26 goals ahead of Sunday''s season-finale at Hull. Son Heung-min also scored twice at the King Power Stadium as Spurs continued to shrug off any disappointment following Chelsea''s title win. The visitors were untouchable as they sealed their 13th win in their last 16 games in all competitions, having already cemented second place.','2017-05-18','0:56:00','http://talksport.com/football/leicester-1-6-tottenham-harry-kane-bags-four-goals-take-charge-golden-boot-race','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (2170,'Sports','/Files/News/News441495175248794.jpg','Football Association confirm they will ban players for diving from 2017/18 season','The Football Association has voted in favour of introducing retrospective bans for players who dive or feign injury from next season. The new offence of ''successful deception of a match official'' is based on a law already used in Scotland and was approved at the FA''s annual general meeting at Wembley on Thursday. Incidents will be reviewed by a panel comprised of an ex-manager, ex-player and an ex-referee, and they watch the footage independently. If they are unanimous in believing a player deceived a match official, the sanction will be a two-match ban.','2017-05-18','3:45:00','http://talksport.com/football/football-association-confirm-they-will-ban-players-diving-201718-season-170518239729','talkSPORT','Active'),
  (2171,'Sports','/Files/News/News451495175249870.jpg','Tyson Fury says date set for Anthony Joshua fight and warns British heavyweight rival: ''I''ll give you a boxing lesson'' - LISTEN','Tyson Fury has promised to teach Anthony Joshua a ''boxing lesson'' after revealing a date has been set for a blockbuster all-British showdown. Speaking to Gareth A Davies for talkSPORT''s Kick Off show, Fury said he remains the number one heavyweight in the world and will prove it when he makes his long-awaited return to the ring. The 28-year-old has not fought since sensationally snatching Wladimir Klitschko''s world titles in November 2015, due to a combination of drug issues and mental health concerns.','2017-05-18','3:27:00','http://talksport.com/boxing/tyson-fury-says-date-set-anthony-joshua-fight-and-warns-british-heavyweight-rival-ill-give','Alex Varney','Active'),
